<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7576&amp;p=75692#p75692"><![CDATA[
For today it's not a big deal to equip a cartridge with alot of ROM. You could easily have a mapper that can use the internal nametables or pick out of something like a 16 megabit (2 megabyte) EPROM giving you plenty of space and unlike mapper 68 you could have separate CHR-ROM and NameTable ROMs. Sp space isn't that much of an issue.<br /><br />Someone made something like a FMV awhile ago that just used CNROM's abailty to have some huge amount of CHR-ROM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Tue Mar 22, 2011 10:33 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
