<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7576&amp;p=75668#p75668</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7576&amp;p=75668#p75668"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Nametable rom]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7576&amp;p=75668#p75668"><![CDATA[
After Burner has to quickly flip through several nametables, and the only way to do that 1. at more than 10 fps, 2. while still moving sprites, and 3. on NTSC without extending blanking, is to put nametables in ROM. That's why After Burner is on <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_068" class="postlink">mapper 68</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Mar 21, 2011 1:53 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
